5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to public K-12 education; to allow a public
10 K-12 school or public charter school to accept a campus
11 chaplain who meets certain requirements as a volunteer; to
12 prohibit certain individuals from volunteering as a campus
13 chaplain; and to allow each local board of education and the
14 governing body of each public charter school to vote on
15 whether to allow the volunteer services of a campus chaplain.
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
17 Section 1. (a) For the purposes of this section, the
18 term "public school" means any public K-12 school or public
19 charter school.
20 (b)(1) Beginning with the 2026-2027 school year, each
21 local board of education and the governing body of each public
22 charter school may take a recorded vote on whether to adopt a
23 policy authorizing a public school under its jurisdiction to
24 accept a campus chaplain as a volunteer under this section.
25 (2) If a local board of education or the governing body
26 of a public charter school votes to accept a campus chaplain
27 as a volunteer, a campus chaplain may be made available to
28 provide support, services, and programs at the request of any
Page 1

provide support, services, and programs at the request of any
HB8 Engrossed
29 teacher in the local school district.
30 (c)(1) A campus chaplain volunteering under this
31 section is not required to be certified by the State Board of
32 Education.
33 (2) Each campus chaplain volunteering under this
34 section must have completed a recognized chaplain training
35 program.
36 (d) A public school that accepts a campus chaplain as a
37 volunteer under this section, before the campus chaplain may
38 begin volunteering, shall ensure that the campus chaplain
39 complies with Section 16-22A-5, Code of Alabama 1975, relating
40 to criminal history background information check requirements.
41 (e) A public school may not accept a campus chaplain as
42 a volunteer who has been adjudicated or convicted of an
43 offense that requires registration as a sex offender under
44 Chapter 20A of Title 15, Code of Alabama 1975.
45 Section 2. This act shall become effective on July 1,
46 2026.
